The paper proposes a visual analytics system to facilitate the exploration of the rich dynamics of CNN training processes, which involves both computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The system is designed to help domain experts with their training tasks in a practical environment, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HCI). The paper also mentions the use of a novel cube-style visualization to reveal complex correlations among multiple types of heterogeneous training data, which could fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
